author: Matt Estreich
title: NBC12/ RVA Sports Network Big 12- Week of October 26
text:
NBC12/ RVA Sports Network Big 12- Week of October 26 - NBC12 - WWBT - Richmond, VA News On Your Side Member Center: NBC12/ RVA Sports Network Big 12- Week of October 26 Posted: Follow @MattNBC12 RICHMOND, VA (WWBT) - 
The top three hold steady in this week's NBC12/RVA Sports Network Big 12 poll but there is a change at #4 after Benedictine's loss: 
1. LC Bird (8-0) - The Skyhawks routed George Wythe 61-0 to hold on to the top spot. (Last week, #1; vs. Huguenot) 
2. Hermitage (8-0) - The Panthers handled Godwin 34-7 to remain unbeaten. (Last week, #2; vs. Glen Allen) 
3. Highland Springs (7-1) - The Springers posted their third straight shutout, beating previous #6 Henrico, 21-0) (Last week,#3; at Patrick Henry) 
4. Douglas Freeman (8-0) - The Rebels topped Deep Run to remain unbeaten. They moved up three spots in this week's poll.(Last week, #7; vs. Godwin) 
5. Monacan (8-1) - The Chiefs also moved up three spots after a shutout win over Midlothian. (Last week, #8; vs. Manchester) 
6. Benedictine (6-1) - The Cadets were knocked from the ranks of the unbeaten by Woodbury Forest and dropped two spots in thisweek's poll. (Last week, #4; vs. Fork Union) 
7. Lee-Davis (7-1) - The Confederates beat then-#9 Hanover in a cross-county rivalry Friday and moved up three spots to #7.(Last Week, #10; at Henrico) 
8. Thomas Dale (6-2) - The Knights were upset by Meadowbrook and dropped three spots in this week's poll. (Last week, #5; vs. Hopewell) 
9. Henrico (6-2) - The Warriors were the latest shutout victim of Highland Springs Friday. (Last Week, #6; vs. Lee-Davis) 
10. Hopewell (6-2) - The Blue Devils shutout Matoaca and moved up one spot in this week's poll. (Last Week, #11; at Thomas Dale) 
11. Manchester (6-2) - The Chiefs bounced back from a loss to Hermitage with a win over Clover Hill. (Last week, #12; at Monacan) 
12. Hanover (5-3) - The Hawks are the only three-loss team in the week's poll after falling to Lee-Davis on Friday. (Last week, #9; at Armstrong)
